    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>When Reality Sets In</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Susan Frierson letter chides couple profiled in April 8 The Hunt column for buying fourth-floor New York City walk-up apartment for retirement years when health may deteriorate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A 59-year-old and his girlfriend (The Hunt, April 8) buy a fourth-floor walk-up to live out their New York City fantasies? That's all fine and good right now, but even a small inevitable surgery or twisted ankle leaves them unable to use it. Do people have no sense?</p>
        <p>Susan Frierson  Upper West Side</p>
      </block>
